      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Arthur Hamilton Gibbs (1888-1964) was a British novelist and essay writer.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">A. Hamilton Gibbs Manuscripts</emph> contains two items, both undated typescript manuscripts for publication. The first item is a 7-page essay entitled "Letter to a Friend," which is about Hamilton's close friend Kenneth Roberts, the American historical fiction author. The essay was published in the <emph render="italic">Colby Library Quarterly</emph> in 1962.</p><p>The second item is a 226-page typescript manuscript of Hamilton's novel <emph render="italic">Obedience to the Moon</emph>, which contains handwritten corrections. A note inside the cover indicates that Gibbs' residence at the time was in Lakeville/Middleboro, Massachusetts. The novel was published in 1956.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
      <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
         <head>Arrangement of the Collection</head>
         <p>Items are in alphabetical order by title.</p>
      </arrangement>
      
